Structured Template for Confluence Page for Pull Request Reviews

This document outlines the required structure for Confluence pages associated with each pull request (PR). Developers must fill out the page for every PR they create. This ensures that all reviewers have complete context and necessary information for efficient and thorough code reviews.

Pull Request Review Documentation Template

PR Title:

	•	Example: feat: Add v3 data preprocessing pipeline

1. Project Overview

Provide an overview of the project or feature the PR is addressing.
	•	Project Name:
	•	Example: V3 Model Development
	•	Purpose:
	•	Example: Implement data preprocessing steps for the v3 model pipeline.
	•	Related JIRA/Trello/Task ID (if applicable):
	•	Example: JIRA-123

2. Purpose of the Changes

Clearly state the purpose of this PR.
	•	Why are these changes being made?
	•	Example: This PR introduces data preprocessing steps to handle missing values, scale numerical features, and encode categorical variables for the v3 model pipeline.
	•	What problem does this solve?
	•	Example: It ensures the dataset is prepared correctly for model training and evaluation.
	•	What specific outcome do we want?
	•	Example: Clean and transformed data ready for input into the v3 model.

3. Requirements Checklist

Document the requirements this PR fulfills. Provide a clear checklist of tasks or conditions related to the feature or code being added.

Requirement	Status	Comments
Handle missing values	✅ Completed	Mean imputation implemented.
Scale numerical features	✅ Completed	StandardScaler applied.
Encode categorical variables	🔲 Pending	Awaiting feature list approval from team lead.

4. Code Changes Summary

Summarize the changes made in the codebase. Include references to specific files or parts of the code.
	•	Files Modified:
	•	preprocessing_pipeline.R
	•	feature_engineering.R
	•	Key Changes:
	•	Added mean imputation for missing values.
	•	StandardScaler for numerical features.
	•	Placeholder for encoding categorical variables.
	•	Lines of Code (LOC):
	•	Added: +200
	•	Deleted: -50

5. Tests and Validation

Provide information about tests conducted for the PR and their results.
	•	Unit Tests:
	•	✅ test_preprocessing.R: Passed
	•	Integration Tests:
	•	🔲 Pending (Scheduled for 2024-11-15)
	•	Edge Case Tests:
	•	✅ Null value handling
	•	🔲 Large dataset scaling
	•	Testing Results Summary:

All unit tests passed. Integration tests scheduled for 2024-11-15. Edge case tests pending final dataset.

6. Developer Comments

Include any additional comments or insights to help reviewers understand the code.
	•	Assumptions:
	•	All numerical columns are standardized with no outliers.
	•	Known Limitations:
	•	Encoding for categorical variables is pending team approval.
	•	Areas for Feedback:
	•	Review logic for scaling and transformation of numerical data.

7. Links to Supporting Materials

Include links to related files, tasks, or documentation.
	•	JIRA Task: JIRA-123
	•	Data Treatment Plan: Confluence Page: Data Treatment for V3
	•	Test Results: Link to Test Outputs
	•	Code Repository: GitHub Link

8. Checklist Before Submission

Developers must verify the following before submitting the PR and page.

Item	Status	Comments
Code compiles and runs locally	✅ Done	No errors or warnings.
All requirements are implemented	✅ Done	Pending encoding approval.
Tests cover the new functionality	🔲 Pending	Scheduled integration tests.
Documentation is complete	✅ Done	Detailed in this Confluence page.
Code follows style guidelines	✅ Done	Adhered to PEP8 for R.

9. Review Guidelines for Reviewer

Provide clear instructions for the reviewer to streamline the process.
	•	Areas to Focus On:
	•	Check data scaling logic.
	•	Verify handling of missing values.
	•	Known Issues:
	•	Encoding not yet implemented.
	•	Expected Time for Review:
	•	1 hour.

10. Action Items for Reviewer

Specify what the reviewer needs to do before approving the PR.

Action	Status	Comments
Review logic in preprocessing	🔲 Pending	Check handling of edge cases.
Verify testing coverage	🔲 Pending	Ensure all edge cases are tested.
Confirm documentation adequacy	🔲 Pending	Feedback on PR template usage.

11. Approvals

List reviewers and approval status.

Reviewer	Role	Approval Status	Comments
Jane Doe	Data Scientist	🔲 Pending	
John Smith	Team Lead	🔲 Pending	

12. Post-Merge Checklist

Outline steps to take after the PR is approved and merged.

Step	Status	Comments
Merge PR into develop branch	🔲 Pending	Only after all approvals are received.
Tag release milestone	🔲 Pending	Use semantic versioning for the tag.
Notify team	🔲 Pending	Update in Slack or Confluence.

By requiring developers to document their PRs in this structured Confluence page, the team can:
	1.	Provide reviewers with complete information.
	2.	Ensure accountability for requirements and tests.
	3.	Streamline the review process and minimize confusion.